<div style="font-size:90%">
<br><br>

<b>2014 February 08 - 09   Shoji Seki Shihan, 8th dan, in Manila</b><br><br><br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<img src="photos/SekiPoster-eventspage.jpg" style="padding:2px; margin:2px; border: 0px solid ; width: 500px; height: 333px;"  vspace="2" alt="SekiPoster"></a>


<br><br>


Seki Shihan, a senior instructor at Japan Aikikai Hombu Dojo, will conduct a seminar in Manila on February 8th and 9th.<br><br>

Seki Shihan is a newly minted 8th dan, having been promoted at the Kagami Biraki ceremony of 2014 January 12th.<br><br>

This first major seminar of 2014 is another joint project of PAPA, FFA, and Aikido Philippines.<br><br>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>

VENUE:<br><br>

PJF dojo, 3d floor, Sports Medicine Bldg., Rizal Memorial Coliseum complex, M. Adriatico St., Malate, Manila<br><br>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>

SEMINAR SCHEDULE:<br><br>

Day 1 of 2:  Saturday, February 08:<br><br>

Session #1: 	1000 - 1115<br><br>

(Lunch break)<br><br>

Session #2: 	1500 - 1615<br>
Session #3: 	1630 - 1745<br><br>

Day 2 of 2:  Sunday, February 09:<br><br>

Session #1: 	1000 - 1115<br><br>

(Lunch break)<br><br>

Session #2: 	1500 - 1615<br>
Session #3: 	1630 - 1730<br>
Session #4:	1745 -1900 (promotion exam)<br><br>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>

SEMINAR CONTRIBUTION:<br><br>

Early-bird package: PhP1,300 (deadline: pay your contribution by midnight of January 25th to your sensei or your federation's designated person)<br><br>

<font color="red">The early bird package for the Seki Shihan seminar has been extended, with a slight increase in price.  Due to popular demand, the deadline is now midnight of Monday, February 3d. The package price is now PhP1,400.</font><br><br>

Daily package:	PhP900 for one day's training (deadline: pay to your sensei or federation officer on or before you enter the training venue)<br><br>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>

DOOR PRIZE:<br><br>

Participants who attend a minimum of three sessions shall be eligible to join a raffle to win one dogi and one new tanto. Therefore, please make sure to sign in at the registration desk for each session that you attend.<br><br>

